message:
fixed using namespace issues:
never include the whole std namespace! always include only exlicit types
f.e. using std::cout; or using std::string;

-adapted X86 code to build again and client code runs now with prototype target
-fixed trace macro
-fixed macros in platform.h

do {...} while(0) is used to omit problems when using a macro like:

if(condition)
  Macro();
else
  doSomething();
-> compile error

works as expected and is no overheat since compiler will optimize do while away

